Package: scSeqR
Type: Package
Title: scSeqR; a toolkit to analyze single sequencing data types (i.e scRNA-seq) and large numeric matrix files.
Version: 0.99.0
Author: Alireza Khodadadi Jamayran 
Maintainer: Alireza Khodadadi Jamayran <alireza.khodadadi.j@gmail.com>
Description: scSeqR is an R package that can analyze single sequencing data types (i.e scRNA-seq) and large numeric matrix files (i.e. count tables with many samples from TCGA). 
  The program inputs single cell data in 10X format, large numeric matrix files and data frames and helps you to perform QC, filtering, visualization, normalization, clustering, differential expression analysis and find positive and negative markers for each cluster.
Depends: R (>= 3.3.0), ggplot2
Imports: Matrix,
  Rtsne, 
  gmp, 
  factoextra, 
  gridExtra,
  ggpubr,
  RColorBrewer,
  pheatmap
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/rezakj/scSeqR
